To create and paste the new `README.md` file in your repository, follow these steps:

1. Go to your repository: [MatrixPlayz4192/sober-manual-Roblox-on-linux](https://github.com/MatrixPlayz4192/sober-manual-Roblox-on-linux)
2. Click on the "Add file" button.
3. Select "Create new file".
4. Enter `README.md` as the filename.
5. Copy and paste the following content into the editor:

```
# Roblox Studio with VinegarHQ on Linux

## Introduction
This guide will help you set up Roblox Studio using VinegarHQ on a Linux system. Follow the steps below to install necessary tools, configure performance FFLAGS, and get started.

## Prerequisites
1. Ensure you have Flatpak installed on your system. You can find installation instructions for your Linux distribution [here](https://flatpak.org/setup/).
2. Visit [VinegarHQ installation guides](https://vinegarhq.org/Installation/guides/package.html) to check your system distro commands.

## Installation

### Step 1: Install Flatpak
Follow the instructions for your Linux distribution on the [Flatpak setup page](https://flatpak.org/setup/).

### Step 2: Install Vinegar
Once Flatpak is set up, install Vinegar using the following command:
```sh
flatpak install flathub org.vinegarhq.Vinegar
```

### Step 3: Run Vinegar
To manually run Vinegar, use the command:
```sh
flatpak run org.vinegarhq.Vinegar
```

## Performance FFLAGS

Add the following FFLAGS to optimize Roblox Studio performance:

```ini
[env]
WINEFSYNC = "1"
WINEESYNC = "1"

[studio]
dxvk = false
renderer = "Vulkan"
gamemode = true

[studio.env]
DXVK_HUD = "0"
MANGOHUD = "1"

[studio.fflags]
DFIntTaskSchedulerTargetFps = 99999  
FFlagTaskSchedulerLimitTargetFpsTo2402 = false   
FFlagGameBasicSettingsFramerateCap5 = false  
```

### Renderer Options
You can change the renderer to one of the following options:
- Vulkan
- D3D11
- D3D10
- OpenGL
- Metal (only for macOS)

## Support
For further assistance, join the VinegarHQ support server on Discord: [VinegarHQ Discord](https://discord.com/invite/dzdzZ6Pps2)
```

6. Scroll down and add a commit message such as "Add README.md for Roblox Studio with VinegarHQ on Linux".
7. Click the "Commit new file" button to save the file to your repository.

This will create and post the `README.md` file in your repository.
